      • power

        public LongInt power(int p)
        Raises the LongInt to the power p (a regular integer) and returns the result as a new LongInt. Note that no more than 2lg(p) calls to multiply are allowed.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        LongInt representing the result from the power
